11 shall complete the current term of office and appointments made
after July 1 of the year in which such modification becomes
12 effective shall be based on the redrawn districts. No appointments
may be made after July 1 of the year in which such modification
13 becomes effective if such appointment would result in more than two
members serving from the same modified district. At least two
14 members must be qualified examiners of a governmental law
enforcement agency and at least two members must be qualified
15 polygraph examiners in the commercial field. The members shall be
appointed by the Governor of the State of Oklahoma, with the advice
16 and consent of the Senate, for terms of six (6) years. Any vacancy
in an unexpired term shall be filled by appointment of the Governor,
17 with the advice and consent of the Senate, for the unexpired term.
