SECTION 34. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 245, as
18 amended by Section 1, Chapter 92, O.S.L. 2023 (74 O.S. Supp. 2025,
Section 245), is amended to read as follows:
19
Section 245. A. The Climate Office of the State of Oklahoma
20 located at Norman, Oklahoma, shall be under the direction and
supervision of the Board of Regents of the University of Oklahoma
21 and shall be known as the Oklahoma Climatological Survey. The
Oklahoma Climatological Survey is hereby re-created, to continue
22 until July 1, 2026, in accordance with the provisions of the
Oklahoma Sunset Law.
23
B. The director of the Oklahoma Climatological Survey shall be
24 appointed by the Board and shall either serve as the state
Req. No. 17604 Page 63

1 clim atologist or appoint another current employee of the Survey to
serve as state climatologist. The salary of the director shall be
2 determined by the Board.
3 C. The Oklahoma Climatological Survey shall have for its object
and duties the following:
4
1. To acquire, archive, process and disseminate, in the most
5 cost-effective way possible, all climate and weather information
which is or could be of value to policy and decision makers in the
6 state;
7 2. To act as the representative of the state in all
climatological and meteorological matters both within and outside
8 the state when requested to do so by the legislative or executive
branches of the state government;
9
3. To prepare, publish and disseminate periodic regular climate
10 summaries for those individuals, agencies and organizations whose
activities are related to the welfare of the state and are affected
11 by climate and weather;
12 4. To conduct and report on studies of climate and weather
phenomena of significant socioeconomic importance to the state;
13
5. To evaluate the significance of natural and man-made,
14 deliberate and inadvertent changes or modifications in important
features of the climate and weather affecting the state, and to
15 report this information to those agencies and organizations in the
state who are likely to be affected by such changes or
16 modifications; and
17 6. To maintain and operate the Oklahoma Mesonetwork, a
statewide environmental monitoring network which is overseen by the
18 Mesonet Steering Committee, comprised of representatives of the
University of Oklahoma and Oklahoma State University according to
19 its Memorandum of Agreement. The director of the Oklahoma
Climatological Survey shall be accountable for executing the
20 policies of the Mesonet Steering Committee.
21 D. The director is authorized to certify copies as being
authentic reproductions of weather records held in the state.
22
E. The director of the Oklahoma Climatological Survey shall
23 present a report each year to the Board of Regents of the University
of Oklahoma showing the progress, condition and all other
24 information which the Board may deem necessary.
