SECTION 38. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 3909, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 3909. A. Except as otherwise provided by law, any
statutory entity listed in Sections 3903 through 3908 of this title
22 which is terminated by the Legislature in accordance with the
Oklahoma Sunset Law shall have a period of one (1) year after its
23 termination date for the purpose of ceasing its affairs and
termination shall not reduce or otherwise limit the powers, duties,
24
Req. No. 17604 Page 66

1 or f unctions of said entity. Upon the expiration of the one-year
period, the entity and its personnel positions shall be abolished.
2
B. Except as otherwise provided by law, one (1) year after the
3 termination date of a statutory entity, the State Treasurer shall
transfer all funds of that entity to the General Revenue Fund. All
4 debts of that entity shall be paid by the State Treasurer from the
funds of that statutory entity. All equipment, files, fixtures,
5 furniture, and supplies of the terminated entity shall be
transferred to the Office of Management and Enterprise Services to
6 be stored or disposed of as specified by law. Any other outstanding
obligations or functions remaining to be performed after termination
7 of an entity shall be performed by the Office of Management and
Enterprise Services until provisions are made for such obligations
8 or functions by the Legislature.
