amended to read as follows:
10
Section 3913. A. All orders, determinations, rules,
11 regulations, permits, certificates, licenses, contracts, rates and
privileges which have been issued, made, granted or allowed to
12 become effective by a statutory entity abolished by the Legislature
pursuant to this act or by any provision of law affected by this
13 act, shall continue in effect according to their terms until
terminated or modified by operation of law.
14
B. Notwithstanding any other provisions of this act any revenue
15 bonds heretofore or hereafter issued or sold by a statutory entity
shall remain in full force and effect, and no such statutory entity
16 shall be terminated under the terms of this act until such
outstanding revenue bonded indebtedness has been satisfied.
17
C. No suit, action or other judicial proceeding lawfully
18 commenced by or against any officer or agency in his or its official
capacity, or in relation to the exercise of his or its official
19 functions, shall abate by reason of the taking effect of any
provision of this act, but the court, unless it determines that the
20 survival of such suit, action or other proceedings is not necessary
for purposes of settlement of the questions involved, shall allow
21 the same to be maintained, with such substitutions as to parties as
are appropriate.
22
D. No administrative action or any judicial proceeding lawfully
23 commenced shall abate solely by reason of the taking effect of any
provision of this act. Any such cause of action pending on the date
24 the entity is terminated or that is commenced during the termination
Req. No. 17604 Page 67

1 peri od shall be prosecuted or defended in the name of the state by
the Attorney General if it would have been his duty to so prosecute
